  <refentry xml:id='function.ibase-blob-open' xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
   <refnamediv>
    <refname>ibase_blob_open</refname>
    <refpurpose>
     Abre um blob para obter partes de dados
    </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
   <refsect1>
    <title>Descrição</title>
     <methodsynopsis>
      <type>resource</type><methodname>ibase_blob_open</methodname>
      <methodparam><type>resource</type><parameter>link_identifier</parameter></methodparam>
      <methodparam><type>string</type><parameter>blob_id</parameter></methodparam>
     </methodsynopsis>
     <methodsynopsis>
      <type>resource</type><methodname>ibase_blob_open</methodname>
      <methodparam><type>string</type><parameter>blob_id</parameter></methodparam>
     </methodsynopsis>
    <para>
     <function>ibase_blob_open</function> abre um BLOB existente para leitura.
     Retorna um handle BLOB para uso posterior com 
     <function>ibase_blob_get</function> ou &false; em caso de falha.
    </para>
    <para>
     Veja também
     <function>ibase_blob_close</function>,
     <function>ibase_blob_echo</function> e
     <function>ibase_blob_get</function>.
    </para>
   </refsect1>
  </refentry>

